Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.00,0:00:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢There was a hungry crow｣
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.00,0:00:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢who somehow wanted to get some feed｣
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.00,0:00:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢if only this beak were longer｣
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.00,0:00:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢that feed would be a bit closer｣
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.00,0:00:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,♪\N～
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.00,0:01:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢a crow can think｣
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.00,0:01:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢can think... can think｣
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.00,0:01:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Observe, propose a hypothesis, experiment and then consider.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.00,0:01:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Lean the way of scientific thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.00,0:01:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,First we start with a ｢Thinking Observation｣
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.00,0:01:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If we flick this pen cap with our finger...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.00,0:01:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Look closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.00,0:01:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, we will be observing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.00,0:01:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Try putting a mark on the cap with a sticker.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.00,0:02:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch the mark when we flick the cap.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.00,0:02:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Flick it once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.00,0:02:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This time we can't see the mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.00,0:02:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we spin it once more...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.00,0:02:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.00,0:02:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the difference between the time when we can see the mark and when we can't?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.00,0:02:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Try spinning it some times.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.00,0:02:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We can see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.00,0:02:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.00,0:03:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.00,0:03:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch carefully the position of our finger when flicking it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.00,0:03:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Flick it on the side we've put the sticker.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.00,0:03:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We can see the mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.00,0:03:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This time flick from the side we haven't put the sticker.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.00,0:03:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't see the mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.00,0:03:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Confirm by placing a mark on the opposite side.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.00,0:03:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Flick on the circle side...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.00,0:03:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't see anything but the circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.00,0:04:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If we flick on the side with the triangle...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.00,0:04:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't see anything but the triangle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.00,0:04:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But the circle and triangle and on the same side.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.00,0:04:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When we can see the circle, we ought not be able to see the triangle at the same time?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.00,0:04:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.00,0:04:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we can only see the circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.00,0:04:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.00,0:04:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,♪\N～
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.00,0:05:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,♪\N～
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.00,0:06:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,♪\N～
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.00,0:06:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Today our problem uses this balloon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.00,0:06:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We affix this balloon to this trolley here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.00,0:06:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When we push this trolley forward...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.00,0:06:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What will happen to the balloon?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.00,0:06:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It tilted backwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.00,0:06:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand this so far, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.00,0:06:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this is the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.00,0:07:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This time we put a transparent box
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.00,0:07:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and push it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.00,0:07:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, before we push the cart...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.00,0:07:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What will happen to the balloon?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.00,0:07:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,1. Like before it will tilt backwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.00,0:07:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,2. It will do the opposite, and tilt forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.00,0:07:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,3. It will remain as it is, and not tilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.00,0:07:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, think really carefully about it, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.00,0:08:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,♪\N～
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.00,0:08:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the answer to our question earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.00,0:08:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you think it through properly?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.00,0:08:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, let's really try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.00,0:09:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.00,0:09:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What will happen to the balloon.\NLook really carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.00,0:09:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.00,0:09:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's look at that once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.00,0:09:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,♪\N～
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.00,0:09:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.00,0:09:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But why do you think that happens?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.00,0:09:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In things there is a property that tries to remain the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.00,0:09:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Covering the balloon with a box and pushing the cart...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.00,0:09:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The air in the box remains in place...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.00,0:09:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,From her on we think for ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.00,0:09:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,From here on we're thinking crows.
